gurmukhi: kmI n kaun kwj kI ]pRBwv rwmrwj kI ]194]
transliteration: Kamina Kaoun Kaaj Kee|| Prabhaav Raam Raaj Kee||194||
translation: In this way there was the sway of Ram Rajya and there was no dearth of anything.194.

gurmukhi: dys dysn kI kiRAw isKvMq hYN idj eyk ]
transliteration: Des Desan Kikriaa Sikhvant Hain Dij Ek||
translation: On one side the Brahmins are teaching about the activities of various countries,

gurmukhi: bwn Aaur kmwn kI ibD dyq Awn Anyk ]
transliteration: Baan Aur Kamaan Kibidh Det Aan Anek||
translation: And on the other side the methods of archery are being reveled.

gurmukhi: BwNq BwNqn soN pVwvq bwr nwr isMgwr ]
transliteration: Bhaant Bhaantan Son Padaavat Baar Naar Singadr||
translation: Instructions are being given about various types of the embellishments of women.

gurmukhi: kok kwbX pVY khUM bXwkrn byd ibcwr ]195]
transliteration: Kok Kaahya Padai Kahoon Bhaakaran Bed Bichaar||195||
translation: The art of love, poetry, grammar and Vedic learning are being taught side by side.195.

gurmukhi: rwm prm pivqR hY rGubMg ky Avqwr ]
transliteration: Raam Param Pavitra Hai Raghoubans Ke Avtaar||
translation: The incarnation of Ram of the clan of Raghu is extremely pure.

gurmukhi: dust dYqn ky sMGwrk sMq pRwn ADwr ]
transliteration: Doust Daitan Ke Saooghaarak Sant Praan Adhaar||
translation: He is the destroyer of tyrants and demons and is thus the support of the life-breath of the saints.

gurmukhi: dyis dyis nrys jIq Asys kIn gulwm ]
transliteration: Des(i) Des(i) Dares Jeet Ases Keen Gulaam||
translation: He has subordinate the king of various countries by conquering them,

gurmukhi: j`qR q`qR Dujw bDI jY p`qR kI sB Dwm ]196]
transliteration: Jattra Tattra Dhujaa Badhijai Pattra Kisabh Dhaam||196||
translation: And his banners of victory are fluttering here, there and everywhere.196.

gurmukhi: bwt qIn idsw iqhUM suq rwjDwnI rwm ]
transliteration: Baat Teen Disaa Tihoon Sout Raajdhaaniraam||
translation: The king gave his three sons the kingdoms of three directions and gave Ram the kingdom of his capital Ayodhya,

gurmukhi: bol rwj ibisst kIn ibcwr kyqk jwm ]
transliteration: Bol Raaj Bisist Keen Bichaar Ketak Jaam||
translation: After discussing for a long time with Vasishtha,

gurmukhi: swj rwGv rwj ky Gt pUr rwKis eyk ]
transliteration: Saaj Raaghav Raaj Ke Ghat Poor Raakhas(i) Ek||
translation: There lived a demoness in the house of Dasrath in disguise,

gurmukhi: AwNbR mauln dIsu audkM Aaur puhp Anyk ]197]
transliteration: Aanbra Maulan Dees(u) Udkan Aur Puhap Anek||197||
translation: Who had asked for all this activity the fructifying mango dust, pure water of the stream and many flowers.197.
